## plot predicted loads across four categories
who <- read.delim("data/world_bank_classifications.txt", header = T)
who$country <- who$country %>% str_replace("United States", "USA")
md.global$geographic_location[md.global$geographic_location == ""] <- NA

for(i in 1:nrow(md.global)){
  keep <- who$country %in% md.global$geographic_location[i]
  if(sum(keep) == 0){
    md.global$developed[i] <- NA
  }else{
    md.global$developed[i] <- who$category[keep]
  }
}

md.global$developed <- md.global$developed %>% factor(levels = c("High income", "Upper-middle income", "Lower-middle income", "Low income"))
pair <- combn(levels(md.global$developed), 2, simplify=F)

md.global2 <- md.global %>% filter(disease == "Control") %>% filter(antibiotics_binary == 0)
p <- md.global2 %>% filter(geographic_location != "NA") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = developed, y = count, fill = developed)) +
  theme_mine() +
  ylab("Predicted load (log10)") +
  geom_violin(aes(fill = developed), col = NA, alpha = 0.6) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.size = -1, width = 0.2, fill = "white") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = tidy_col) +
  ggpubr::stat_compare_means(comparisons = pair, tip.length = 0, method = "wilcox.test", size = 2) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank(), legend.position = "none") +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 30, hjust = 1, vjust = 1))

df <- md.global %>% filter(days_since_antibiotics != "")

df <- md.global %>% filter(study == "Palleja_2018_antibiotics" | study == "Raymond_2016_antibiotics")
md.ab1 <- md.global %>% filter(study == "Palleja_2018_antibiotics")
md.ab2 <- md.global %>% filter(study == "Raymond_2016_antibiotics")

temp1 <- data.frame(name = md.ab1$subject_id, time = md.ab1$timepoint, count = md.ab1$count, study = md.ab1$study, shannon = md.ab1$shannon)
temp2 <- data.frame(name = md.ab2$subject_id, time = md.ab2$timepoint, count = md.ab2$count, study = md.ab2$study, shannon = md.ab2$shannon)
df <- rbind(temp1, temp2) %>% data.frame()
df$time <- factor(df$time, levels = c("0", "4", "7", "8", "42", "90", "180"))

df <- df %>% arrange(time)
df$study2 <- df$study %>% 
  str_replace("Palleja_2018_antibiotics", "Palleja 2018") %>% 
  str_replace("Raymond_2016_antibiotics", "Raymond 2016")

df1 <- df %>% filter(study == "Palleja_2018_antibiotics")
df2 <- df %>% filter(study == "Raymond_2016_antibiotics")

df1$time <- df1$time[drop = T]
df2$time <- df2$time[drop = T]

pair <- list(c("0", "4"), c("0", "8"), c("0", "42"), c("0", "180"))

## manually add three missing samples for paired test
temp.df <- df1 %>% filter(time == "4") %>% head(n = 3)
temp.df$name <- c("ERAS1", "ERAS10", "ERAS8")
temp.df$count <- NA
